    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Cancer Transformation - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_cancer_transformation">Cancer Transformation</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_malignant_abnormality">MALIGNANT ABNORMALITY</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_cancer_transformation">Cancer Transformation</xref>
 is the process by which 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_cell">CELLS</xref>
 acquire the properties of cancer.        </p>
      <p>
This may occur as a primary process in normal 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_tissue">TISSUE</xref>, or secondarily as malignant degeneration of a previously existing benign 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_tumour">Tumour</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
For further information on 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_cancer_transformation">Cancer Transformation</xref>, see the 
              <xref href="https://www.cancer.gov/publications/dictionaries/cancer-terms?CdrID=46628"
               scope="external"
               format="html">National Cancer Institute website</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
